ratings.question_text: Overall, how would you rate the workload of this course in comparison to other Yale courses you have taken?
What is your overall assessment of this course?
Do you expect to use this class for credit toward your major, or toward a pre-professional program?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Its an intermediate Spanish class taught similarly to L1 and L2 Spanish at Yale. I would recommend it if you enjoy spanish.
The grammar is mostly a repeat of L2. There are a lot of course packet readings that are pretty interesting and hard.
Good course. If had previous spanish knowledge, this would be a good course to start off with because it provides a review, as well as learning new material.
I would recommend this class if you need to fill the requirement.
It is a useful class if you have it with a worth while teacher.

This was a great couse. If you have to take it, definitely take it with Oscar. He is the man. He is very relaxed and a great teacher. You might have to review a little by yourself for the assessments, but if you do the work you should get a good grade.
